<html><head></head><body><b>Hans Geiger (1882–1945)</b><br/>
A German physicist. He was a professor at the university <br/>in Kiel, Tübingen and Berlin. Geiger conducted research on radioactivity, dispersion <br/>of charged particles <br/>and cosmic radiation. He constructed a particle counter which in 1926 was improved by W. Müller (Geiger-Müller counter). In 1911, together with a British physicist J.M. Nuttall, he stated the empiric law of radioactive decay (Geiger-Nuttall Law).
</body></html>